    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="to"
                            >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-11T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 11, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. For <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Reber</persName>. Your telegram 184, May 10,
                    5 p.m. You are authorized to use any method which seems the most desirable in
                    cooperating with the British, French and possibly the German representatives <pb
                        facs="0816" n="726" xml:id="pg_726"/> in bringing the <persName
                        corresp="#p_RDG1">Rydings</persName> report before the Committee. If a joint
                    statement is submitted, I believe it should clearly state that the findings are
                    entirely the work of a British official and should describe the origin of his
                    investigations.</p>
                <p>The Firestones recently received a radio from <persName corresp="#p_HWD2"
                        >Hines</persName> to the effect that he had been told that the <persName
                        corresp="#p_RDG1">Rydings</persName> report contained certain unfriendly
                    references to <persName corresp="#p_FHSS1">Firestone</persName> interests in
                    Liberia. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Mitchell</persName>’s telegraphic
                    summary to us on April 30 makes no reference whatever to any mention of the
                    Firestones, and we accordingly told them that we thought <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWD2">Hines</persName> had been misinformed. I mention this
                    matter to you merely in order that you may definitely ascertain that nothing of
                    this sort is contained in the report prior to your participation in any joint
                    submission which could not fail to indicate a general agreement on our part with
                    the text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
